After each stimulus, D1 and D2 were multiplied by constants d1 and d2, representing the amount of depression per presynaptic action potential (i.e. D1 → D1d1, and D2 → D2d2). Between stimuli, D variables recovered exponentially back towards 1 with first-order kinetics governed by recovery time constants τD1 and τD2:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
